30083009.descripe: An undisciplined youth and an icy assassin that often rely on wholly unexpected methods of attack in combat.

30123019.descripe: Polymerized-type Visbanes that appear simultaneously. Good at using clones to fight and are extremely dangerous.

30213022.descripe: Special entities that appear during Quakes, they are remnants of the Soul Replenishment Plan.

401001.descripe: A man who lost all his memories and woke up in some ancient ruins, on a pile of rubble and spare parts. 80% of his body tissues have been changed into machinery.

401201.descripe: The original design of a human-shaped B-01 was abandoned. At last, Kusherfang was modified into the form of a centaur, equipped with a giant halberd.

401301.descripe: Halphas is a Cognizant-type Visbane that appeared in the Source Layer of the Neuhansa District. It was heavily affected by the industrialization on the Surface Layer and has a massive mechanical body.

401401.descripe: Dressed in the splendid garments of a kabuki, her eyes show nothing but contempt for all things, and she is always accompanied by giant snakes.

401501.descripe: Humanoid Visbane. Looks more like a mermaid and is often accompanied by a Visbanic whale.

402001.descripe:
A very rare Behemoth Type Visbane among all observed Visbanes, codenamed "Haagenti". The cause of its formation is unknown for the time being.
It is assumed that it's formed as a result of the massive engulfment of Source Layer material by the Visbane. It is quite large and possesses destructive power that exceeds that of ordinary Visbanes.

402101.descripe: A unique Behemoth Type Visbane resembling a cyclops. Both its hands seem to contain mountains of energy.

402801.descripe: This type of military mecha utilizes the most advanced AI technology and a new-developed propulsion system, allowing it to cope with a wide variety of complex battlefield situations and providing extreme mobility.

402902.descripe:
A giant weapon that was corrupted by Bane Energy in the Quakes. It showed more of the characteristics of Visbane compared to machinery, and became incomparably berserk.
After the drive energy was changed to Bane Energy, its combat ability was greatly improved, and ordinary attacks could not cause damage to it.

403101.descripe:
Conceived from the Paracaesar's Project Forgetower, it is an Artificial Modifier with the ability to control the "past."
"None can escape the destiny that's been set for them. The time has come to meet the ending I've written for you."

402501.descripe:
A Visbane born in Omorfies, he has the appearance of a mythical dragon.
"Get ready to meet the mighty Ladon in his true form!"

40264027.descripe: A Behemoth-type Visbane that appears near the Peripheral Sea who can direct the ocean's currents and control storms.

40234024.descripe: The current commander of the Knights of Convallaria, she is a person of moral integrity who upholds the chivalric values of justice and loyalty. She has made it her lifelong mission to safeguard artistic order in Omorfies.

403601.descripe: A Cognizant Visbane born in Xu Heng's Source Layer that has concealed itself in society for a while. It has used its beauty and intelligence to move up and thrive in the business world.

301601.descripe:
Affected by the aftershock of the Quakes, the Source Layer channel cannot be closed within a short time.
In order to overcome the crisis, please defeat the small Visbane group as soon as possible. Search for and destroy the high-level Visbane that are in command.

301901.descripe:
Chase the Visbanes into the Source Layer Lair to exterminate them and the battle will be extremely rough.
Be careful with the large number of Encroacher Type Visbanes and look out for attacks by high-risk Polymerized Type.

300601.descripe:
The factory has been infested by the Visbanes. Take control back from the Visbane-corrupted AGI Mechas.
Visbane-corrupted AGI Mechas are highly autonomous and will continue to produce small AGI Mechas. Eliminate them as soon as possible.

301001.descripe:
The security team stationed here has severely affected the completion of the mission. Disable its combat ability as soon as possible.
Target has team fighting ability. If you are sieged, you will be in danger.

303501.descripe:
Compete with members of The Knights of Convallaria to show "friendship".
In order to guard the art of Omorfies, it is sometimes unavoidable to draw the sword.

302001.descripe:
Simulate the environment of an invasion combat to evaluate the combat level of the customized AGI Mecha.
As a temple of art in Omorfies, those who have no reverence for art will be turned away.

302501.descripe:
A riot breaks out on the stage of the festival. Protect the public while eliminate the Visbanes.
Crisis often lurks underneath the beautiful exterior. Perhaps a dance is the beginning of chaos.

303301.descripe:
Fight against Bounty Hunter at the abandoned station. Pay attention to the terrain and the enemy's autonomous weapons.
There are many ways to solve problems, but in Rostach, the only way to survive is to survive.

300701.descripe:
Sasanami is in turbulence. The hidden Source Layer Rift is opened, indicating the wrath of the speechless one.
Wandering through the phantoms of war and unable to free itself, this body has been drenched with scarlet blood.

300401.descripe:
Even though already a half-human, half-bane monster, he is still sworn to guard all the secrets of the Miyahebi family.
Anyone who trespasses will be beheaded.

300911.descripe:
An undisciplined youth and an icy assassin that often rely on wholly unexpected methods of attack in combat.
"You'd better not hinder me."
"Excuse me? I should say that to you. We'll see!"

302211.descripe:
Special entities that appear during Quakes, they are remnants of the Soul Replenishment Plan.
With souls and memories being tainted, they can no longer be defined as "human" and are just empty shells.

301411.descripe:
The traveling painter and loyal vassal have gone long time ago, and now all that remains are obnoxious monsters.
After the fire, there will be nothing left but ashes.

301311.descripe:
Strong Bane Energy signals have been detected, presumed to be multiple special Visbane entities. Please be careful.
Trouble always comes one after another.

401111.descripe:
A man who lost all his memories and woke up in some ancient ruins, on a pile of rubble and spare parts. 80% of his body tissues have been changed into machinery.
As the leader of Children of Iron, he acts very lazy and always makes others feel unpredictable.

401221.descripe:
A huge centaur-type AGI Mecha weapon, which was declared as an unsurpassed existence in "individual combat".
For the maker of Kusherfang, it was more like an unsurpassed work of art before it became a weapon of destruction.

402901.descripe:

Twin puppets that typically serve as maids at the Society of Muses where they take care of the members' day-to-day needs, though in combat they turn into fearsome weapons in the hands of Hades.
"It's time to clean up."

17701.descripe: A massive mechanoid Visbane. Its body is equipped with a terrifying quantity of weapons with heavy firepower, and can sweep the battlefield with explosions when it enters the fray.

17801.descripe: An individual born from the aggregation of a certain number of corrupted species. It uses a large sword and shield to execute powerful offensive and defensive measures. Extra attention should be paid when fighting it due to its high risk level.

17901.descripe: A special Encroacher Type Visbane and a failed product of the Soul Replacement Plan, it was formed when its soul and memories were corrupted by Turing's Bane Energy.

18101.descripe: A bipedal combat vehicle with standard military armor. Capable of showering enemies with a hail of firepower.

18201.descripe: A specialized Polymerized Type variant that emerged in response to the environmental conditions created by Cloudsong Ore. It's adept at attacking using a combination of swordplay and Bane Energy.

18301.descripe: A former Akishika family subordinate bewitched into becoming the backbone of the zealots. Uses the Bane Energy in the flag during battle to launch magic attacks on the enemy.

22315.descripe: The security captain stationed here has caused the mission to be seriously impeded. He has to be knocked down as soon as possible to make him lose his combat effectiveness.

22316.descripe: A fusion of machinery and biotechnology that Seema calls the "Fist of Revenge."
